
Question 3. What is an operating system and give examples. Also, discuss its main functions
and responsibility

Answer:--->
An Operating System is an interface between a computer user and computer hardware. An operating system is a software which
performs all the basic tasks like memory management, process management, input and output, and
controlling  devices  those devices that are linked either internally or externally to a computer.(disk drives and printers)


some Operating Systems are :-
1)  Linux
2)  Windows
3)  Android


  functions of an operating System:----


  File Management
  Proessor Managemnet
  Security
  Job Accounting
  Coordination between other software and users
  Memory Management
  Device Management


 Memory Management:-
                    The term Memory can be defined as a collection of data in a specific format.
Memory management refers to management of Primary Memory or Main Memory, In main memeory there  are large number of  bytes which have its own address.



File Management:---
                   File Management is use for file maintenance operations, its manage the data files in a computer system
                    It has limited capabilities ans designed to manage individual or group of files

Device Management:----
                  Device Management in OS means controlling the I/O devices like microphone,keyboards, printer, Scanner




