Question 2:-

What is CAP theorem, discuss a scenario where CAP theorem helps you choose a
technology over the other or helps you make a design decision.

Answer:-
The CAP theorem is a belief from theoretical computer science about distributed data stores that claims, in the event of a network failure on a distributed database,
it is possible to provide either consistency or availabilityâ€”but not both.

any distributed system guarantees any two of the three stated later.
1)  Consistency  (All reads receive the most recent write or an error.)
2)  Availability (All reads contain data, but it might not be recent.)
3)  Partition Tolerance (the system continues to operate despite arbitrary message loss or failure of
    a part of the system).


